00:42:01.650 --> 00:42:06.920
&gt;&gt; Male #1: So I guess you sort of mentioned
this when you talked about the meat and three.

00:42:06.920 --> 00:42:11.380
I'm from Virginia; I lived in DC for a long
time so I'm pretty familiar with southern

00:42:11.380 --> 00:42:12.380
food.

00:42:12.380 --> 00:42:17.720
Was flipping through your book and it looks
wonderful but everything is really heavy.

00:42:17.720 --> 00:42:20.180
Everything is really cooked.

00:42:20.180 --> 00:42:21.760
Everything is stewed; everything is fried.

00:42:21.760 --> 00:42:26.980
How do you sort of square that with, you know,
stuff you'd want to eat every day.

00:42:26.980 --> 00:42:32.020
How does the southern food tradition sort
of fit into something you could actually live

00:42:32.020 --> 00:42:33.020
with.

00:42:33.020 --> 00:42:36.220
[laughter]
&gt;&gt;Hugh: I think that, you know, it's everything

00:42:36.220 --> 00:42:38.790
in moderation as Julia used to say.

00:42:38.790 --> 00:42:43.160
You know, it is a rich sort of philosophy
of food.

00:42:43.160 --> 00:42:48.020
But interspersed with that are going to be
soups and salads that should take more of

00:42:48.020 --> 00:42:50.980
a prominence in a meal than people think.

00:42:50.980 --> 00:42:52.829
And on the table.

00:42:52.829 --> 00:42:58.510
But then you look at the use of -- no use
of lard and there is some use of bacon fat

00:42:58.510 --> 00:42:59.710
and things like that.

00:42:59.710 --> 00:43:04.010
But everything -- the food I do is generally
much lighter than it appears to be.

00:43:04.010 --> 00:43:13.030
So I think that, you know -- but southern
food is based around pretty gut-sticking ideals.

00:43:13.030 --> 00:43:19.410
But I think that idea of southern food takes
into consideration that the sort of Paula

00:43:19.410 --> 00:43:23.690
Deen mentality that southern food began and
ended at a certain time and we need to show

00:43:23.690 --> 00:43:25.220
a reverence to that.

00:43:25.220 --> 00:43:26.339
I don't believe that.

00:43:26.339 --> 00:43:27.670
I don't believe it's ended yet.

00:43:27.670 --> 00:43:33.890
I believe there's a sort of cultural impact
wonderful other communities moving into that

00:43:33.890 --> 00:43:37.030
area that are going to have change on that
food.

00:43:37.030 --> 00:43:41.460
There's a health consciousness that happens
slowly but surely and influences that food.

00:43:41.460 --> 00:43:44.310
I think it will alter those dishes for the
better.

00:43:44.310 --> 00:43:47.890
I just think it's a slow road but I think
you're seeing it.

00:43:47.890 --> 00:43:52.770
And I think if you look closely at the recipes
in the book, they're lighter than they appear.

00:43:52.770 --> 00:43:54.710
